com.camerontec.catalys.server.test

Class EmbeddedAdapterStatelessRouterBenchmark

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.test.EmbeddedAdapterStatelessRouterBenchmark
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFIXListenerCallback, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IAccumulator

    public class EmbeddedAdapterStatelessRouterBenchmark
extends Object
implements IFIXListenerCallback, IAccumulator
    Simple EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter based application which measures the stateless routing of a FIX message through two FIX sessions (one inbound and one outbound).

    Inbound messages are timestamped as soon as they are recognised as FIX messages (T1) on the inbound session and then another timestamp is prior the message being sent on the socket of the outbound session. Each latency sample is thus (T2 - T1) nanoseconds.

    On receipt of every 2^20 messages the sample histogram is displayed on the stderr stream and the internal histogram is reset.

      • configure

        public void configure(IConfiguration configuration)
               throws ConfigurationException
        Description copied from interface: IConfigurable
        Apply the IConfiguration to this IConfigurable.

        This method is called by the configuration module in the server:

        • when loading the configuration at server startup (e.g. when reading the XML configuration file) and
        • every time we reload the configuration object corresponding to the configurable run-time object.
        The Catalys Server passes a reference to a configuration clone. The original reference is unavailable to the configurable object. The configurable object may decide to store the reference as the last valid configuration object which can be used to optimize the re-configuration.
        Specified by:
        configure in interface IConfigurable
        Parameters:
        configuration - the immutable configuration object
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException - This exception is thrown when the new configuration object cannot be applied to the configurable object.
